Common English name: Southern bluespotted flathead (
Figs. 11–12
;
Table 4
)

Distribution. Known from southern Australia , from Cape Everard, Vic (
149 ° 16 ’E
) to Kalbarri, WA (
27 ° 42 ’S
), including Tas and SA, mainly on shallow sand patches among seagrasses in bays and large estuaries in depths from 1 to 30 m (e.g.,
Last et al ., 1983
;
Hoese et al ., 2006
;
Gomon, 2008
; this study).

Size. Maximum length 90 cm (
Last et al ., 1983
). The largest specimen examined in the present study was 493 mm SL ( 577 mm TL) (
Fig. 11
).
